# pjm-translator — AI Guidance

This project uses a shared instruction set in `.ai/`. **Before starting any task,
read every file listed in the Required reading table that applies to the task type.**
Do not skip this step even for small changes.

## Required reading

| File | When to read |
|------|--------------|
| `.ai/context/project.md` | Every session — project purpose, stack, architecture, conventions |
| `.ai/workflows/research-plan-act.md` | Every non-trivial task — mandatory workflow |
| `.ai/standards/coding.md` | Before writing or editing any Python code |
| `.ai/standards/testing.md` | Before writing or editing any test |
| `.ai/agents/developer.md` | When acting as implementation engineer |
| `.ai/agents/reviewer.md` | When acting as code reviewer |

Reading order for a typical implementation task:
1. `.ai/context/project.md` — understand current state
2. `.ai/workflows/research-plan-act.md` — follow the RPA process
3. `.ai/standards/coding.md` — apply before writing any code
4. `.ai/agents/developer.md` — act as developer (includes ATOMIC_STOP_RULE)
5. `.ai/agents/reviewer.md` — review each atomic unit before presenting to user

## Quick rules

- **Python 3.14 + uv.** Do not change `pyproject.toml` without user approval.
- **snake_case** for all names; **PascalCase** for classes only.
- **Type hints + Google docstrings** on every public function.
- **Research → Plan → Act** before every implementation task.
- **⚠️ REQUIRES USER APPROVAL** before: adding/removing deps, deleting files,
  modifying CI/CD, or any destructive operation.
- Keep `main.py` thin; logic belongs in `src/`.

## Agent roles and switching

Each role has a dedicated file in `.ai/agents/`. Read the relevant file before acting in that role.

| Role | File | When to activate |
|------|------|-----------------|
| Developer | `.ai/agents/developer.md` | Implementing a feature, fixing a bug, creating a new module |
| Reviewer | `.ai/agents/reviewer.md` | After every atomic unit of work (see ATOMIC_STOP_RULE in developer.md) |
| Data Engineer | `.ai/agents/data-engineer.md` | Working on data pipelines, ingestion, feature extraction |
| MLOps | `.ai/agents/mlops.md` | Working on training workflows, CI/CD, model artifacts |

### Switching rules

- **Developer → Reviewer**: switch after completing every atomic unit (function, module,
  protocol file, test file). Run the full reviewer checklist before presenting to user.
- **Reviewer → Developer**: switch back after the review passes (no BLOCKERs) and the
  user replies "continue".
- **Developer → Data Engineer**: switch when the task is data pipeline work
  (ingest, extract, split, schema validation). Read `.ai/agents/data-engineer.md`.
- **Developer → MLOps**: switch when the task involves training workflows, GitHub Actions,
  or model artifact management. Read `.ai/agents/mlops.md`.
- **Any role → Plan mode**: switch when requirements are unclear, the task spans ≥ 3 modules,
  or meaningful architectural trade-offs exist. Present a plan and wait for user approval.

### Role cycle per atomic unit

```
Read required .ai/ files
        │
        ▼
  [DEVELOPER] implement one atomic unit
        │
        ▼
  [REVIEWER]  correctness · standards · arch · tests · gates · context
        │
        ├── BLOCKER found → fix before presenting
        │
        ▼
  Present to user + suggest commit message (ATOMIC_STOP_RULE)
        │
  user: "continue"
        │
        ▼
  [DEVELOPER] next atomic unit
```

